=comment Package: Gtk4, C-Source: shortcutaction
use v6.d;

=begin pod
=TITLE Gnome::Gtk4::T-shortcutaction
=end pod

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#--[Bitfields]------------------------------------------------------------------
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

=begin pod
=head1 Bitfields

=head2 GtkShortcutActionFlags

List of flags that can be passed to action activation.

More flags may be added in the future.

=item C<GTK_SHORTCUT_ACTION_EXCLUSIVE>; The action is the only
  action that can be activated. If this flag is not set,
  a future activation may select a different action.
=end pod

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#--[Callback Functions]---------------------------------------------------------
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

=begin pod
=head1 Callback Functions
=head2 ShortcutFunc

=head3 Signature
=begin code
:(  N-Object() $widget, N-Object $args, gpointer $user-data  )
=end code

=item $widget; The widget passed to the activation
=item $args; The arguments passed to the activation
=item $user-data; The user data provided when activating the action

=end pod
